"&#xa0;\n&#xa0;&#xa0;Written evidence from the Chartered Institute of Logistics and Transport in the UK (SRN 047)&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nIntroduction&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nThe Strategic Road Network&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nHow will the policies set out in the Government’s “Action for Roads” command paper improve the strategic road network for all road users, whilst also improving the environment?&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nHow reliable is the Government’s forecast for growth in demand for the strategic road network? How should the Government deal with uncertainty in its forecast?&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;How does the Government’s policy for roads link with planning for other transport modes?&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nWhat mechanisms are there for Government to increase investment in strategic roads and attract new investors? Are there good examples from other countries that could be applied in the UK?&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nKey Lessons from the Paying for Better Motorways Initiative&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n. \nPrivate funding for the strategic network as a whole&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nHow should the Highways Agency be reformed to make it “the world’s leading highway operator”? What roles should Government and the private sector play to ensure better management of the strategic road network?&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nOctober 2013 \n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n  It is not clear whether the Government’s figures include annual payments under existing PFI schemes. These were forecast in the Department of Transport’s “Transport Report 1997” to amount to some £250million in 1999 and have presumably grown since. \n See the summary at Annex B.\n \nDfT\n Road Transport Forecasts 2013. Results from the Department for Transport’s National Transport Model\n “On the Move” Scott Le Vine and Peter Jones, University College London 2012\n Labour Party Review, September 2013\n \nHouse of Commons (2007) Treasury Committee, \nMemorandum submitted by T. Martin \nBlaiklock\n.\n \n&#xa0;\n Providing and Funding Strategic Roads, RAC Foundation and Arup, November 2011\n"